INSECURE.Definition: insecure people have little confidence and are uncertain about their own abilities or if other people really like them

GET MY MESSAGE ACROSS.Definition: to manage to make someone understand or believe something

FORMER.Definition: the first of two people, things, or groups previously mentioned

LATTER.Definition: the second of two people, things, or groups previously mentioned

GENERALIZING.Definition: to make a general statement that something is true in all cases, based on what is true in some cases

VOLUNTARILY.Definition: in a voluntary way (= done, made, or given willingly)

CAPABLE.Definition: able to do things effectively and skillfully, and to achieve results

CONSISTENT.Definition: always behaving or happening in a similar, especially positive, way

DEFER.Definition: to delay something until a later time

GRATIFICATION.Definition: pleasure or satisfaction, or something which provides this

REWARD.Definition: something given in exchange for good behavior or good work, etc.

INCREASES.Definition: to become or make something larger or greater

TURNING ONE'S LIFE AROUND.Definition: to stop living in a negative, self-destructive way; to change your life completely, from a bad lifestyle to a good lifestyle

ARROGANT.Definition: unpleasantly proud and behaving as if you are more important than, or know more than, other people

GENIUS.Definition: very great and rare natural ability or skill, especially in a particular area such as science or art, or a person who has this

WORK HIS ASS OFF.Definition: a rude phrase meaning to make someone work very hard

BLOOD, SWEAT, AND TEARS.Definition: extremely hard work, or the greatest effort possible, in order to achieve something

REALIZED.Definition: to achieve something you were hoping for

LIFESTYLE.Definition: someone's way of living; the things that a person or particular group of people usually do

MENTALITY.Definition: a person's particular way of thinking about things

CHASE.Definition: to try very hard to persuade someone to have a relationship with you

ENDURANCE.Definition: the ability to keep doing something difficult, unpleasant, or painful for a long time

AGILITY.Definition: the ability to move your body quickly and easily

UNSTOPPABLE.Definition: unable to be stopped or prevented from developing

GETTING IN SHAPE.Definition: to work to have good, robust health; to become strong or fit

SOCIAL FUNCTIONS.Definition: an official ceremony or a formal social event, such as a party or a special meal, at which a lot of people are usually present

ENGAGING.Definition: tending to draw favorable attention or interest

WALLOW.Definition: to wallow in an emotion or situation is to stay in that state without trying to change

SELF-PITY.Definition: pity for oneself especially : a self-indulgent dwelling on one's own sorrows or misfortunes

OBSESS.Definition: if something or someone obsesses you, or if you obsess about something or someone, you think about it, him, or her all the time

SHORTCOMINGS.Definition: a fault or a failure to reach a particular standard

INVESTING.Definition: to put money, effort, time, etc. into something to make a profit or get an advantage

PRODUCTIVE.Definition: causing or providing a good result or a large amount of something

TAKE A LONG, HARD LOOK AT YOURSELF.Definition: to examine something very carefully in order to improve it in the future

TOXIC.Definition: causing you a lot of harm and unhappiness over a long period of time
